<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Crystal Palace are leading the chase to sign Chelsea midfielder Conor Gallagher on loan.</p>

<p>The 20-year old is close to agreeing a new long term contract with Chelsea before going out on a temporary move for the season.</p>

<p>A number of Premier League sides, including Leeds and Newcastle, have expressed interest in the energetic England U21 international who impressed on loan at Swansea City last season.</p>

<p>Crystal Palace are leading the chase to sign Chelsea midfielder Conor Gallagher on loan</p>

<p>Palace though have been eager to convince Gallagher to join them and have instigated talks with Chelsea and the player's representatives.</p>

<p>The 20-year-old came on as a second-half substitute for injured summer signing Hakim Ziyech in Chelsea's 1-1 draw with Brighton in a friendly on Saturday.</p>

<p>Gallagher's current deal at Stamford Bridge runs until 2022 but any fears over his long-term future at the club appear to be over.</p>

<p>Gallagher featured against Brighton and is close to signing a new deal before going on loan</p>

<p>The midfielder moved to Wales in January after spending the first half of the season at Charlton.Â </p>

<p>Gallagher played 19 times to help Steve Cooper's Swansea, who finished 6th and set up a play-off semi against Brentford.</p>

<p>But despite winning the first leg 1-0, Swansea collapsed at Griffin Park to lose 3-2 on aggregate.</p>
